ere is an external world (macrocosm) and there is an int=\r\nernal world (microcosm). They resonate with each other and influence each o=\r\nther.\n=C2=A0\nThe external world consists of real people with their own mind=\r\ns, conditioning and agendas. The internal world consists of our mental mode=\r\nls of those people. As a matter of fact, though we think that we are dealin=\r\ng with the external world, there is very little that we know about it. The =\r\nworld we mostly live in is the internal world. I&#39;ll elaborate.\n=C2=A0\nOur s=\r\nenses capture *some* aspects of the objective reality of the external world=\r\n. But that is a very small part of the reality. For example, one&#39;s ears may=\r\n hear another person saying something. One&#39;s eyes may see another person ha=\r\nving a particular facial expression. And so on. Like connecting dots to mak=\r\ne a nice picture, we *interpret* these sensory inputs based on the conditio=\r\nning in our chitta! Thus, one forms a mental image of what the other person=\r\ns are thinking and feeling, what their attitudes and priorities are, etc. O=\r\nur internal world is filled with such models of many many people. We essent=\r\nially live in that internal world!\n=C2=A0\nThe interface between the externa=\r\nl and internal worlds is very minimal. External world influences the intern=\r\nal world through inputs from one&#39;s jnanendriyas (senses of perception). Int=\r\nernal world influences the external world through actions/outputs of one&#39;s =\r\nkarmendriyas (organs of action). The resonance I mentioned works through th=\r\nis thin interface. Changes happening in the internal world eventually refle=\r\nct on the external world, and vice versa.\n=C2=A0\nWe like, dislike, get frus=\r\ntrated by, resist and admire the characters in the internal world. Our atti=\r\ntudes towards these characters in the internal world reflect in our externa=\r\nl actions, which get noticed by the corresponding characters in the externa=\r\nl world.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nThe key to controlling the external=\r\n world is in controlling the internal world. The key to controlling the int=\r\nernal world is in recognizing the paramount role of one&#39;s own conditioning =\r\nin *moulding* the internal world. In the end, it all boils down to self-con=\r\ntrol and overcoming one&#39;s conditioning.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nLet us=\r\n get back to the specific example mentioned below. Suppose I want to do hom=\r\nam regularly and my room mate may not like it. From the words uttered by my=\r\n room mate (as heard by my ears) and the facial expressions shown (as seen =\r\nby my eyes), possibly on several occasions, I can come to a limited objecti=\r\nve understanding of his attitude and thinking. I may know that he is not pl=\r\neased. Forming a more complete picture of what he thinks, wants and why, is=\r\n akin to connecting dots to make a nice picture. One can paint a whole rang=\r\ne of possible pictures within what one knows objectively. But, one&#39;s condit=\r\nioning pushes one to pick a few possibilities out of those. We do that all =\r\nthe time without being conscious of it.\n=C2=A0\nSuppose I am conditioned to =\r\nbe proud of the religious work I do and to think that some evil forces may =\r\nstop me in my good work. The desire to do homam itself is not a problem, bu=\r\nt this undesirable conditioning can be a problem. When someone shows disple=\r\nasure at my doing homam in the room, my conditioning may push some wrong bu=\r\nttons in me (!) and trigger resentment. A negative character with a lot of =\r\nfriction with me is propped up in my internal world! My thoughts, words and=\r\n actions will project (physically and also subtly) that character and its f=\r\nriction with me, onto the external world through resonance. The other perso=\r\nn may become even more negative than before, as a result of resonance with =\r\nmy internal world. As both parties act as slaves of their conditioning and =\r\nact without self-control, things can snowball and there can be an environme=\r\nnt of great resentment and friction.\n=C2=A0\nThis is kind of like moviemaker=\r\ns depicting violence and gore excessively, saying that they are only reflec=\r\nting what is happening in society, while society being influenced by movies=\r\n and engaging in even more violence and then moviemakers pushing the envelo=\r\npe further, and so on.\n=C2=A0\nSuppose I am devoid of much negative conditio=\r\nning and all I want is to do homam if possible. When someone shows displeas=\r\nure, that will then not press any wrong buttons in me and trigger any resen=\r\ntment. I will note the fact that they have some displeasure. Because my vis=\r\nion is not clouded with conditioning (to be proud of my work and look at pe=\r\nople creating obstacles as evil people), I may be able to understand their =\r\nperspective better. On the balance, I may still choose to go ahead and do h=\r\nomam, but without much resentment in my mind. The character propped up in m=\r\ny mind may not be a very negative one and not have much friction with me. I=\r\n may love this character from my internal world, feel compassionate about i=\r\nt, understand its motivations and yet do my homam. Then my thoughts, words =\r\nand actions will project (physically and also subtly) that nice character a=\r\nnd my love for it, onto the external world through resonance. Even if the o=\r\nther person is more\n negative than I realized, influence of (resonance with=\r\n) my internal world will eventually change him for better. (It will atleast=\r\n not make him worse!!)\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nI am not talking about =\r\nbeing stupid here or cheating oneself. If someone says &quot;I don&#39;t like your a=\r\nctions&quot;, I am not saying that one should think &quot;he loves me and he is sayin=\r\ng I am great&quot;. What I am suggesting is to stick to objective facts (as perc=\r\neived by sensory mind) and create as positive a picture from the objective =\r\nfacts as possible. Of course, one&#39;s conditioning (i.e. the momentum from al=\r\nl previous experiences and karmik debts) makes it difficult. If one&#39;s condi=\r\ntioning pushes one to create as negative a picture from the objective facts=\r\n as possible about someone, resisting that push and forming as positive a p=\r\nicture from the objective facts as possible is not easy.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nOne word on suprressing feelings and forcing nice behavior may=\r\n be appropriate here.\n=C2=A0\nSuppose one&#39;s wife says harsh things to one an=\r\nd fights. Suppose one resents it and thinks &quot;I am being so nice and accommo=\r\ndating. Why is she so mean to me&quot;. If one suppresses that feeling and force=\r\ns nice behavior, that is good only temporarily. The character of wife in on=\r\ne&#39;s inner world is still a negative one. One&#39;s thoughts about that characte=\r\nr are still &quot;I am being so nice and accommodating. Why is she so mean to me=\r\n&quot;. The suppressed resentment will blow off oneday and result in a bigger fi=\r\nght/argument.\n=C2=A0\nIf one really wants improvement, then the character of=\r\n wife in one&#39;s inner world needs to be transformed. One can try to put ones=\r\nelf in the shoes of wife and try to figure out the picture is from her side=\r\n. Most people in this world are not 100% terrible. They are an amalgam of g=\r\nood and bad. Perhaps one&#39;s wife actually loves one and one&#39;s words conveyed=\r\n to her that he is not happy and her sub-conscious disappointment at not be=\r\ning to make husband happy showed up externally as an outburst. So many such=\r\n possibilities exist. People&#39;s external actions don&#39;t always reflect the de=\r\nepest motivations. Attachments make people act strangely. Some people who f=\r\neel a deep attachment to us may act harsh with us.\n=C2=A0\nIf one can put on=\r\neself in the shoes of wife and come up with a more compassionate explanatio=\r\nn of her behavior and attribute as positive motivations to her behavior as =\r\npossible, then one&#39;s notions about the character of wife in the inner world=\r\n will improve. Then one may be able to behave nicely without suppressing an=\r\ny feelings! This is more sustainable in the long-term. As the character of =\r\nwife in the inner world becomes nicer and nicer, it will reflect in one&#39;s e=\r\nxternal behavior with the corresponding person in the external world. This =\r\nwill eventually impact the thinking of wife (in external world) and reflect=\r\n in her behavior with one.\n=C2=A0\nThrough one&#39;s actions and the other perso=\r\nn&#39;s actions, slowly the discrepancies between a character in one&#39;s inner wo=\r\nrld and one&#39;s outer world come down and the two characters come close to ea=\r\nch other. So you transform the outer world character by transforming the in=\r\nner world character. This is really the only way you can control the extern=\r\nal world on a sustainable basis.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nIf you think=\r\n carefully, you will see that all qualities of characters in our inner worl=\r\nd are partly dependent on objective sensory observations (of the correspond=\r\ning characters in the external world) and partly dependent on our subjectiv=\r\ne conditioning. The latter is by no means trivial. In fact, it is often the=\r\n larger factor.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nI said that the interaction b=\r\netween external and internal worlds is through jnanendriyas and karmendriya=\r\ns. One may assume that these are physical organs (e.g. physical eyes, physi=\r\ncal ears etc). That&#39;s not true. For example, the karmendriya of speech not =\r\nonly covers vaikhari (physical speech), but subtler forms of speech (para, =\r\npasyanti, madhyama). Similarly, the jnanendriya of hearing not only covers =\r\nhearing vaikhari speech, but those subtler forms too. Same with vision etc.=\r\n\n=C2=A0\nIf I am looking at someone with great admiration or great resentmen=\r\nt, the subtle sabda generated by my thoughts is accessible to subtle hearin=\r\ng of that person. That becomes an interface between my internal and externa=\r\nl worlds. My admiration or resentment for a character in my inner world aff=\r\nects the &#39;sabda&#39; produced by me (by subtle thoughts and imagery in the mind=\r\n, as well as physical speech) and that sabda in time reaches (and may affec=\r\nt the inner world of) the corresponding character in the external world.\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------------------------------------------=\r\n-----------------------\n=C2=A0 Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons,=\r\n Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitr=\r\ni Tarpana:\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.o=\r\nrg\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Spirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/ved=\r\nic-wisdom\n=C2=A0 Jyotish writings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWri=\r\ntings\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Twitter ID: @homam108\n-=\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------\n=C2=A0\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nOn Fri, Mar 9, 2012 at 5:15 AM, aswin kumar wrote:\n\nWhat is wrong in=\r\n having good agenda like doing havan regualrily \n\nthough friends in=C2=A0 o=\r\nur=C2=A0 room may not like that=C2=A0 \nIn this case can I drop the idea of =\r\ndoing havan \n\n\n___________________________________\n\nFrom: Narasimha PVR Rao=\r\n &lt;pvr@...&gt; \nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \nSent: Friday, 9 March=\r\n 2012 5:51 AM \nSubject: [vedic-wisdom]=C2=A0 Liberation, Control & Love \n\n=\r\n=C2=A0 Namaste friends, \n\nI recently finished a specific sadhana of a speci=\r\nfic form of Divine \nMother. This particular goddess, according to my guru, =\r\nattracts others \nto a sadhaka and gives &quot;control and mastery&quot; over others. =\r\n\n\nI want to share what I realized towards the end of sadhana, because that =\r\n\nrealization MAY be helpful to some others. \n\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n\nDIFEERENT T=\r\nRAJECTORIES \n\nThere are beings that can give specific limited things, but t=\r\nhe ultimate \ngoal of sadhana is liberation and sadhana of higher beings eve=\r\nntually \ntransforms one and takes one closer to liberation. What these high=\r\ner \nbeings are supposed to give in tradition is a simplificaation or \nsymbo=\r\nlism of something sublime that takes towards liberation, from \n*different a=\r\nngles*. \n\nFor example, ability to work very hard (with no expectations of a=\r\nnything \nselfish in return), fine judgment and discrimination (that increas=\r\nes \ndetachment in one&#39;s actions), complete surrender to god (and \nwhole-hea=\r\nrted acceptance of every life situation one finds oneself in), \nability to =\r\nfocus mind (on a mantra or a deity and not let various \nthoughts distract i=\r\nt), are all useful to a sadhaka. If one develops one \nof these 4 basic qual=\r\nities, other qualities will eventually develop. \nThey all lead to the same =\r\nthing - liberation - in the end, but the \ntrajectory is different. \n\nThese =\r\nfour basic paths constitute what are known as karma yoga \n(communion throug=\r\nh action), jnana yoga (communion through wisdom), \nbhakti yoga (communion t=\r\nhrough devotion) and raja yoga (communion \nthrough [self-]control). However=\r\n, there are many sub-paths. \n\nBasically, different higher beings can increa=\r\nse a different fine quality \ninside one, which is conducive to liberation. =\r\nThe trajectory is \ndifferent with each deity. \n\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n\nTOO MUND=\r\nANE? \n\nThe higher being I worshipped is supposed to increase control and \nm=\r\nastery over others. While I did the sadhana in the last few months, I \nwond=\r\nered how *that* can lead to liberation. After all, control and \nmastery ove=\r\nr others sounded too *mundane* to me to have anything to do \nwith liberatio=\r\nn. But a simple realization came towards the end of the \nsadhana. \n\n*=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 * \n\nCONTROL & FRICTION \n\nWhether A is attracted to B or B is attract=\r\ned to A, the bottomline is \nthat objects A and B come together. The ability=\r\n to attract others also \nmeans to come together with them. \n\nOne is unhappy=\r\n with others and thinks of controlling them, when one&#39;s \nown agenda is mis-=\r\naligned with their agenda. The friction between the \nagendas is the basis f=\r\nor the entire dynamics of likes, dislikes, \nfrustrations etc. Control of th=\r\nat friction comes when the agendas are \nnicely aligned! \n\nAbility to contro=\r\nl the agenda pursued by someone else has limited use, \nscope and lifetime. =\r\nSuch an ability can work only with a limited set of \npeople or a limited am=\r\nount of time. This is like pumping rainwater from \nthe fields surrounding a=\r\n hill to the top of the hill. It requires a lot \nof energy that is proporti=\r\nonal to the area of the field and the amount \nof rainwater. \n\nThe best way =\r\nto avoid the friction, with ALL beings of the cosmos, is to \neliminate one&#39;=\r\ns own agenda! This is like removing the hill from the \nmiddle of the field,=\r\n in the above analogy. \n\nIf one has no agenda whatsoever, then there is no =\r\nfriction with anyone&#39;s \nagenda. There is no reason to like or dislike anyon=\r\ne or find fault with \nor admire anyone. One can just observe others. Becaus=\r\ne one has no \nagenda, one can identify with the agendas of others and relat=\r\ne to them \ncompletely. One can then put oneself completely in the shoes of =\r\nothers \nand feel their pleasures, pains etc. \n\nWhen one has an agenda and a=\r\nnother has another agenda, then there is \nfriction and one feels a need to =\r\n&quot;control&quot; and remove friction. But, \nwhen one has no agenda and another has=\r\n an agenda, then there is no \nfriction. One can then completely &quot;understand=\r\n&quot; the perspective of the \nother (because there is no friction from one&#39;s ow=\r\nn agenda stopping one \nfrom doing so!). What better mastery and control can=\r\n one have on someone \nelse than be able to understand that person completel=\r\ny?! \n\nThough what I described above is the end, one path to that end is to =\r\n\nidentify one&#39;s own agenda/conditioning that is resulting in friction, \nwhe=\r\nnever one is not happy with someone, and try to remove/suppress that \ncondi=\r\ntioning. One can first try this with a few people (e.g. spouse). \n\n*=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 * \n\nLOVE & COMPASSION FOR ALL \n\nBottomline is this: Control and mast=\r\nery over others does not mean making \nthem think and behave in tune with th=\r\ne agenda of one&#39;s own limited \nconditioning. Instead, it means overcoming&#39;s=\r\n one&#39;s own agendas and being \nable to put oneself in the shoes of anybody a=\r\nnd understand and feel each \nof their feelings and emotions. It means uncon=\r\nditional love and \ncompassion for all. \n\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n\nLOOKING DOWN ON O=\r\nTHERS \n\nWhen one is doing some sadhana, one of the stages one goes through =\r\nmay \nbe to feel proud of one&#39;s sadhana, look at some others doing such a \ns=\r\nadhana favorably or with admiration and look down on others who are not \ndo=\r\ning much sadhana (or doing a different sadhana!) and pursuing mundane \nthin=\r\ngs. This may be a natural tendency, but realize that this is a work \nof the=\r\n limited personality or ego. \n\nOne has to overcome that tendency, for looki=\r\nng down on others will \neventually block one. \n\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n\nLOVING T=\r\nHE DIVINE MOTHER \n\nPeople talk of loving the Divine Mother. The personality=\r\n of Divine \nMother is beyond one&#39;s perception. How can one really love Her =\r\nthen? \n\nOne may do tremendous sadhana and get tremendous visions and think =\r\nthat \none has grasped the personality of Divine Mother, but what one percei=\r\nves \nis merely what one&#39;s conditioning fancies and is capable of grasping! =\r\n\nThe complete personality of Divine Mother is beyond anybody&#39;s \nperception.=\r\n \n\nHowever, Divine Mother does manifest in a perceptible way as the cosmos.=\r\n \nEvery being in the cosmos is a limited manifestation of Her. Being able \n=\r\nto love every being is the FIRST step in truly loving the Divine Mother. \n\n=\r\nLoving someone because they are doing some good work (as we see it!) or \nbe=\r\ncause they have something we need (as we see it!) etc, is *egoistic* \nlovin=\r\ng. Such love is *conditioned* by the agendas of a limited ego. Such \nlove c=\r\nannot extend to entire cosmos and permanently. The only love that \ncan exte=\r\nnd to entire cosmos and be permanent is unconditional love of \nall beings. =\r\n\n\nThat comes only when one has no agenda and no expectations from anyone. \n=\r\n\nBest regards, \nNarasimha \n------------------------------------------------=\r\n---------- \nFree Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings, =\r\n\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana: \nhttp:/=\r\n/www.VedicAstrologer.org\nFilms that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilm=\r\ns.org\nSpirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\nJyotish writ=\r\nings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\nTwitter ID: @homam108 \n=\r\n---------------------------------------------------------- \n\n\n \r\n--4813690-482946932-1331524387=:31810\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;html&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:#000; background-color:#fff; font-family:ti=\r\nmes new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;After read=\r\ning your explanation I could remember thesaying of swami vivekananda&lt;/span&gt;=\r\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&quot;conquer yourself you can conquer the whole world&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;=\r\n/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family: times new roman,new york,t=\r\nimes,serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family: times new roman,n=\r\new york,times,serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; =\r\nface=3D&quot;Arial&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;From=\r\n:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=\r\n=3D&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com &lt;br&gt; &lt;b=\r\n&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Monday, 12 March 2012 =\r\n6:12 AM&lt