reas=\r\nes or decreases.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;=\r\n#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=\r\n=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div a=\r\nlign=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/f=\r\nont&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Ve=\r\nrdana&quot;&gt;I&#39;ll go back to something I mentioned before. There is an external w=\r\norld (macrocosm) and there is an internal world (microcosm). They resonate =\r\nwith each other and influence each other.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;=\r\nfont size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div =\r\nalign=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;The exte=\r\nrnal world consists of real people with their own minds, conditioning and a=\r\ngendas. The internal world consists of our mental models of those people. A=\r\ns a matter of fact, though we\n think that we are dealing with the external =\r\nworld, there is very little that we know about it. The world we mostly live=\r\n in is the internal world. I&#39;ll elaborate.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;=\r\n&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div=\r\n align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Our sen=\r\nses capture *some* aspects of the objective reality of the external world. =\r\nBut that is a very small part of the reality. For example, one&#39;s ears may h=\r\near another person saying something. One&#39;s eyes may see another person havi=\r\nng a particular facial expression. And so on. Like connecting dots to make =\r\na nice picture, we *interpret* these sensory inputs based on the conditioni=\r\nng in our chitta! Thus, one forms a mental image of what the other persons =\r\nare thinking and feeling, what their attitudes and priorities are, etc. Our=\r\n internal world is filled with such models of many many people. We essentia=\r\nlly live in that internal\n world!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font siz=\r\ne=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D=\r\n&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;The interface be=\r\ntween the external and internal worlds is very minimal. External world infl=\r\nuences the internal world through inputs from one&#39;s jnanendriyas (senses of=\r\n perception). Internal world influences the external world through actions/=\r\noutputs of one&#39;s karmendriyas (organs of action). The resonance I mentioned=\r\n works through this thin interface. Changes happening in the internal world=\r\n eventually reflect on the external world, and vice versa.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div=\r\n align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;=\r\n/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;=\r\nVerdana&quot;&gt;We like, dislike, get frustrated by, resist and admire the charact=\r\ners in the internal world. Our attitudes towards these characters in the in=\r\nternal world reflect in our external actions, which\n get noticed by the cor=\r\nresponding characters in the external world.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT=\r\n&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;d=\r\niv align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp; *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000=\r\n&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; =\r\ncolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;The key to controlling the external worl=\r\nd is in controlling the internal world. The key to controlling the internal=\r\n world is in recognizing the paramount role of one&#39;s own conditioning in *m=\r\noulding* the internal world. In the end, it all boils down to self-control =\r\nand overcoming one&#39;s conditioning.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font si=\r\nze=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot;\n face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=\r\n=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Let us get back to the specific example menti=\r\noned below. Suppose I want to do homam regularly and my room mate may not l=\r\nike it. From the words uttered by my room mate (as heard by my ears) and th=\r\ne facial expressions shown (as seen by my eyes), possibly on several occasi=\r\nons, I can come to a limited objective understanding of his attitude and th=\r\ninking. I may know that he is not pleased. Forming a more complete picture =\r\nof what he thinks, wants and why, is akin to connecting dots to make a nice=\r\n picture. One can paint a whole range of possible pictures within what one =\r\nknows objectively. But, one&#39;s conditioning pushes one to pick a few possibi=\r\nlities out of those. We do that all the time without being\n conscious of it=\r\n.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=\r\n=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Suppose I am conditioned to be proud of the r=\r\neligious work I do and to think that some evil forces may stop me in my goo=\r\nd work. The desire to do homam itself is not a problem, but this undesirabl=\r\ne conditioning can be a problem. When someone shows displeasure at my doing=\r\n homam in the room, my conditioning may push some wrong buttons in me (!) a=\r\nnd trigger resentment. A negative character with a lot of friction with me =\r\nis propped up in my internal world! My thoughts, words and actions will pro=\r\nject (physically and also subtly) that character and its friction with me, =\r\nonto the external world through resonance. The other person may become even=\r\n more negative than before, as a result of resonance with my internal world=\r\n. As both parties act as slaves of their conditioning and act without\n self=\r\n-control, things can snowball and there can be an environment of great rese=\r\nntment and friction.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font =\r\nsize=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;This is kind of like moviemak=\r\ners depicting violence and gore excessively, saying that they are only refl=\r\necting what is happening in society, while society being influenced by movi=\r\nes and engaging in even more violence and then moviemakers pushing the enve=\r\nlope further, and so on.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; c=\r\nolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;f=\r\nont size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Suppose I am devoid of mu=\r\nch negative conditioning and all I want is to do homam if possible. When so=\r\nmeone shows displeasure, that will then not press any wrong buttons in me a=\r\nnd trigger any resentment. I will note the fact that they have some displea=\r\nsure. Because my\n vision is not clouded with conditioning (to be proud of m=\r\ny work and look at people creating obstacles as evil people), I may be able=\r\n to understand their perspective better. On the balance, I may still choose=\r\n to go ahead and do homam, but without much resentment in my mind. The char=\r\nacter propped up in my mind may not be a very negative one and not have muc=\r\nh friction with me. I may love this character from my internal world, feel =\r\ncompassionate about it, understand its motivations and yet do my homam. The=\r\nn my thoughts, words and actions will project (physically and also subtly) =\r\nthat nice character and my love for it, onto the external world through res=\r\nonance. Even if the other person is more negative than I realized, influenc=\r\ne of (resonance with) my internal world will eventually change him for bett=\r\ner. (It will atleast not make him worse!!)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;=\r\n&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div=\r\n\n align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp; *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot;=\r\n face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; c=\r\nolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;I am not talking about being stupid here =\r\nor cheating oneself. If someone says &quot;I don&#39;t like your actions&quot;, I am not =\r\nsaying that one should think &quot;he loves me and he is saying I am great&quot;. Wha=\r\nt I am suggesting is to stick to objective facts (as perceived by sensory m=\r\nind) and create as positive a picture from the objective facts as possible.=\r\n Of course, one&#39;s conditioning (i.e. the momentum from all previous experie=\r\nnces and karmik debts) makes it difficult. If one&#39;s conditioning pushes one=\r\n to create as negative a picture from the objective facts as possible about=\r\n someone, resisting that push and forming as positive a picture from the ob=\r\njective facts as\n possible is not easy.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;fo=\r\nnt size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div al=\r\nign=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np; *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; fac=\r\ne=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;One word on suprressing feelings and forcing =\r\nnice behavior may be appropriate here.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;fon=\r\nt size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div ali=\r\ngn=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Suppose one=\r\n&#39;s wife says harsh things to one and fights. Suppose one resents it and thi=\r\nnks &quot;I am being so nice and accommodating. Why is she so mean to me&quot;. If on=\r\ne suppresses that feeling and forces nice behavior, that is good only tempo=\r\nrarily. The character of wife in one&#39;s inner world is\n still a negative one=\r\n. One&#39;s thoughts about that character are still &quot;I am being so nice and acc=\r\nommodating. Why is she so mean to me&quot;. The suppressed resentment will blow =\r\noff oneday and result in a bigger fight/argument.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D=\r\n&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/d=\r\niv&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=\r\nIf one really wants improvement, then the character of wife in one&#39;s inner =\r\nworld needs to be transformed. One can try to put oneself in the shoes of w=\r\nife and try to figure out the picture is from her side. Most people in this=\r\n world are not 100% terrible. They are an amalgam of good and bad. Perhaps =\r\none&#39;s wife actually loves one and one&#39;s words conveyed to her that he is no=\r\nt happy and her sub-conscious disappointment at not being to make husband h=\r\nappy showed up externally as an outburst. So many such possibilities exist.=\r\n People&#39;s external actions don&#39;t always reflect the deepest\n motivations. A=\r\nttachments make people act strangely. Some people who feel a deep attachmen=\r\nt to us may act harsh with us.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=\r\n=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;=\r\nLEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;If one can put on=\r\neself in the shoes of wife and come up with a more compassionate explanatio=\r\nn of her behavior and attribute as positive motivations to her behavior as =\r\npossible, then one&#39;s notions about the character of wife in the inner world=\r\n will improve. Then one may be able to behave nicely without suppressing an=\r\ny feelings! This is more sustainable in the long-term. As the character of =\r\nwife in the inner world becomes nicer and nicer, it will reflect in one&#39;s e=\r\nxternal behavior with the corresponding person in the external world. This =\r\nwill eventually impact the thinking of wife (in external world) and reflect=\r\n in her behavior with one.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;=\r\n\n color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;=\r\n&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Through one&#39;s actions =\r\nand the other person&#39;s actions, slowly the discrepancies between a characte=\r\nr in one&#39;s inner world and one&#39;s outer world come down and the two characte=\r\nrs come close to each other. So you transform the outer world character by =\r\ntransforming the inner world character. This is really the only way you can=\r\n control the external world on a sustainable basis.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;=\r\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdan=\r\na&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D=\r\n&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font siz=\r\ne=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;If you think carefully, you will=\r\n see that all qualities of characters\n in our inner world are partly depend=\r\nent on objective sensory observations (of the corresponding characters in t=\r\nhe external world) and partly dependent on our subjective conditioning. The=\r\n latter is by no means trivial. In fact, it is often the larger factor.&lt;/fo=\r\nnt&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Ver=\r\ndana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000=\r\n000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font =\r\nsize=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;I said that t=\r\nhe interaction between external and internal worlds is through jnanendriyas=\r\n and karmendriyas. One may assume that these are physical organs (e.g. phys=\r\nical eyes, physical ears etc). That&#39;s not true. For example, the karmendriy=\r\na of speech not only covers vaikhari (physical speech), but\n subtler forms =\r\nof speech (para, pasyanti, madhyama). Similarly, the jnanendriya of hearing=\r\n not only covers hearing vaikhari speech, but those subtler forms too. Same=\r\n with vision etc.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D=\r\n&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font siz=\r\ne=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;If I am looking at someone with =\r\ngreat admiration or great resentment, the subtle sabda generated by my thou=\r\nghts is accessible to subtle hearing of that person. That becomes an interf=\r\nace between my internal and external worlds. My admiration or resentment fo=\r\nr a character in my inner world affects the &#39;sabda&#39; produced by me (by subt=\r\nle thoughts and imagery in the mind, as well as physical speech) and that s=\r\nabda in time reaches (and may affect the inner world of) the corresponding =\r\ncharacter in the external world.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=\r\n=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div\n align=3D=\r\n&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Best regards,&lt;/f=\r\nont&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Ve=\r\nrdana&quot;&gt;Narasimha&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;=\r\n#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;-------------------------------------------------=\r\n------------------&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;fon